#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code sliding window use karta hai longest substring nikalne ke liye
jise at most k replacements se same character wala bana sakein.

1. Window [left ... right] maintain karte hain.
2. hash array se current window me har character ki frequency store karte hain.
3. maxFreq current window ke kisi bhi character ki maximum frequency batata hai.
4. Agar window length - maxFreq > k ho,
   matlab itne characters replace karne padenge jo k se zyada hain,
   to window invalid ho gayi, isliye left ko aage badha dete hain.
5. Agar valid hai, to current window length se maxLen update karte rehte hain.

Main idea:
Agar window me sabse frequent character maxFreq baar aa raha hai,
to baaki sab characters ko replace karke poori window same bana sakte hain.
Required replacements = window size - maxFreq

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int characterReplacement(String s, int k) {

        int n = s.length();
        int left = 0;
        int right = 0;
        int[] hash = new int[26];

        int maxFreq = 0;
        int maxLen = 0;

        while (right < n) {

            hash[s.charAt(right) - 'A']++;
            maxFreq = Math.max(maxFreq, hash[s.charAt(right) - 'A']);

            if ((right - left + 1) - maxFreq > k) {
                hash[s.charAt(left) - 'A']--;
                left++;
            }

            maxLen = Math.max(maxLen, right - left + 1);
            right++;
        }

        return maxLen;
    }
}
